A patient whose identity could not be ascertained committed suicide at the University of Benin Teaching Hospital (UBTH) on Saturday night. It was gathered that the incident occurred at the Accident and Emergency (A & E) Ward of the hospital It was further gathered that the victim committed suicide with a broken louvre while waiting for a doctor to attend to him. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Daily Trust further learnt that the deceased’s wife went to buy items at a nearby shop within the hospital’s premises when the incident happened. A witness said they don’t know what might have happened that made him to commit suicide. ” While waiting for the doctor, the man suddenly became wild and stabbed himself to death with a broken louvre”, he said. Responding, the spokesman of UBTH, Joshua Uwaila, said it happened on Saturday night at the male ward of the hospital. “An unfortunate incident happened on Saturday night July 13, at about 10:30 pm when a young man who was a patient at the male medical ward of our hospital suddenly broke a louvre and stabbed himself,”. ” All efforts to resuscitate him proved abortive as he was certified dead at 11:00 pm. The result of autopsy is being awaited at the moment,” he said. UBTH doctor found dead in hotel Kaduna: Woman caught for stealing 9 months sick baby in a hospital Students top list as 42 Nigerians commit suicide in 6 months Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin